data.name: label2.Text
data.value: The Dewey Decimal System organizes information into 10 broad areas, which are broken into smaller and smaller topics. Different topics are assigned numbers, known as 'call numbers'. For example 'Tigers' are given the number 599.756. To see what books the library currently has in on tigers, go the nonfiction shelves and find the books that have that number on their spine label.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: When you click on Start Game button below, a new window will pop up and you will be tasked with having to reorder books based on their call number. A timer will count up to 60 and at 60 seconds you will run out of time. The order being smallest numbers first, until the biggest call number. If you make a mitake you can either reset the game or reorder the books on the top panel.
